---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Learn more about Jen O'Hara and her approach to interior design.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero" style="min-height: 50vh; padding: 6rem 2rem;">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align: center;">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Bio Section -->
  <section class="designer-section" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="designer-grid">
        <div class="designer-image">
          <div style="width:100%;height:100%;background:linear-gradient(135deg, #d4c5b5 0%, #b8a999 100%);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;color:#888;font-size:0.85rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;">Jen's Photo</div>
        </div>
        <div class="designer-content">
          <h4>The Designer</h4>
          <h2>Jen O'Hara</h2>
          <p>For nearly two decades, I've had the privilege of helping clients transform their houses into homes—spaces that feel authentically theirs, where beauty and everyday life coexist in harmony.</p>
          <p>My path to interior design wasn't linear. After years in [previous field], I found myself increasingly drawn to the way spaces shape how we feel, work, and connect with the people we love. That curiosity became a calling, and eventually, a career I pour my heart into every day.</p>
          <p>What drives me is the belief that a home should never feel precious or untouchable. Yes, I obsess over proportions, fabrics, and the perfect shade of white—but always in service of creating rooms where you can actually curl up with a book, where children can play, where the dog is welcome on the sofa.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Quote -->
  <div class="quote-block">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <blockquote>"I believe the best interiors tell a story—your story. Not a showroom, not a trend report, but a reflection of how you actually live and what you truly love."</blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Approach -->
  <section style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h4 style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.2em; color: var(--color-taupe); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-weight: 400;">Design Philosophy</h4>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">An Approach Built on Listening</h2>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Every project begins with conversation. Before we discuss colors or furniture, I want to understand how you start your mornings, where you gather with family, what frustrates you about your current space. These details shape everything that follows.</p>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">I'm drawn to interiors that feel collected rather than decorated—rooms that look like they evolved over time, filled with pieces that have meaning. This means blending antiques with contemporary furniture, mixing high and low, and always choosing quality over quantity.</p>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">While I appreciate timeless elegance, I never want a space to feel like a museum. Homes are meant to be lived in. The wear on a vintage table, the patina on brass hardware, the softness of well-loved linen—these are the details that make a house feel like home.</p>
      
      <h4 style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.2em; color: var(--color-taupe); margin: 3rem 0 1rem; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-weight: 400;">Working Together</h4>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">A Collaborative Process</h3>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">My clients often describe me as calm, collaborative, and detail-obsessed (in a good way). I take the stress out of the design process so you can enjoy watching your home transform. From initial concept through final styling, I'm there every step of the way.</p>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Based in the New York area, I work with clients throughout Connecticut, Westchester, and Manhattan. Whether you're renovating a historic home, decorating a new build, or simply refreshing a room that isn't working, I'd love to hear about your project.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Services Preview -->
  <section class="section-cream" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 3rem; text-align: center;">
        <div>
          <h4 style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--color-taupe); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-sans);">Full-Service Design</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 280px; margin: 0 auto;">Comprehensive design from concept through installation. We handle every detail.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--color-taupe); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-sans);">Room Refresh</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 280px; margin: 0 auto;">Focused redesign for a single space that needs new life and direction.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--color-taupe); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-sans);">Consultation</h4>
          <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 280px; margin: 0 auto;">In-home session to discuss your space and leave with a clear plan.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Contact CTA -->
  <section class="contact-section" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>Let's Talk</h2>
      <p>Ready to create a home that's truly yours?</p>
      <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <a href="mailto:jen@jenoharainteriors.com" class="btn">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
